```

If this payload is inserted by the attacker, it would execute when other users visit the web page, alerting them with a popup message.

### How Output Encoding in React Prevents XSS

To mitigate such attacks, developers can use output encoding techniques. In the context of a React application, this means encoding user input before displaying it on the page to ensure that any special characters do not interfere with the HTML structure and are interpreted as data rather than executable code.

